OL,3,CThe tax choice facing NI farmers
OL,5,F"They (the government) have brought
OL,6,Fthese proposals in, genuinely without
OL,7,Fthinking about it and not realising
OL,8,Fthe knock-on effect," he said.
OL,10,FHe added that he was worried about the
OL,11,F'long-term' effects on farmers and
OL,12,Fother industries.
OL,14,FOne way farms can be exempt from the
OL,15,Fnew proposals is if the family farm is
OL,16,Fgifted, but the donor must live on it
OL,17,Ffor seven years thereafter.
OL,19,FTimothy Kinnear was forced into
OL,20,Fadapting, not by his own choice.
